htm9 | Trials which are too small are highly unlikely to produce conclusive results particularly for realistic moderate effects. Such trials could be considered unethical by exposing patients to a trial which has little chance of being able to address a clinically meaningful question.
8hul | It is helpful to produce tabulations under different scenarios. Realistic evaluation is needed to as to whether a trial is feasible given the resources both in terms of costs and patient availability.
